        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 4:58PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles west of Two Buttes Reservoir, or 21 miles northwest of
Springfield, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pritchett and Two Buttes Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
